ZH: 我的老师很喜欢讲故事。
EN: My teacher likes to tell stories.

ZH: 他喜欢在公共场合大声讲话。
EN: He likes to speak loudly in public.

ZH: 她很有耐心地讲解每一个问题。
EN: She patiently explains every question.

ZH: 孩子们都很喜欢听老师讲课。
EN: The children all enjoy listening to the teacher's lessons.

ZH: 请你不要在课堂上讲电话。
EN: Please do not make phone calls in class.

ZH: 你要讲英语或者中文？
EN: Do you want to speak English or Chinese?

ZH: 他不能讲中文，只会讲英语。
EN: He cannot speak Chinese, only English.

ZH: 请你讲慢一点，我听不懂。
EN: Can you speak slower? I don't understand.

ZH: 他是个好老师，很会讲笑话。
EN: He is a good teacher and tells jokes well.

ZH: 在这个会议上，我们讲了很多重要事情。
EN: At this meeting, we discussed many important matters.

ZH: 她讲了很多关于中国历史的故事。
EN: She told many stories about Chinese history.

ZH: 这本书讲了一个很感人的故事。
EN: This book tells a very touching story.

ZH: 这个领导喜欢讲座谈会，和大家一起讨论问题。
EN: This leader likes to hold symposiums and discuss issues with everyone.

ZH: 请不要在图书馆里大声讲话。
EN: Please do not speak loudly in the library.

ZH: 他每天都会讲一段英语对话。
EN: He practices an English dialogue every day.

ZH: 这位年轻教授讲起课来非常有趣。
EN: This young professor is very interesting when lecturing.

ZH: 这个网红喜欢在自己的频道里讲烹饪技巧。
EN: This internet celebrity likes to talk about cooking skills on her channel.

ZH: 我们在会议上讲了关于环境问题的严重性。
EN: We discussed the seriousness of environmental issues at the meeting.

ZH: 老师讲了很多考试的重要知识点。
EN: The teacher covered many key points for the exam.

ZH: 这个节目讲述了一个令人感动的爱情故事。
EN: This program tells a touching love story.
